30/07/2010
By Sasa Ilic for Southeast European Times in Belgrade -- 30/07/10
Aiming to promote free media in the country, the International Research and Exchanges Board programme is part of an $8m USAID project. 
According to organisers, one way to channel the media "in the right direction" is to educate staffers on formatting stations' music matrixes, improving radio imaging and advertisement production. 
 "What we've learned here will help us in the future to guide our media in the right direction," said Goran Vladkovic, owner and editor-in-chief of OK Radio in Vranje. 
